$interpreted: Jerome: Queen... Diana?
Kittyeyes: Eh? Did you just say something, Jerome?
Jerome: Ah... I said, that woman is dressed quite, um, beautifully.
Kittyeyes: Oh, yeah. Very beautiful.
Diana: Thank you for the compliment, Jerome of the Kingdom of the Sun. Now, I think it would be more convenient for us to speak inside. I'll be waiting.
Kittyeyes: Oh, so you know her?
Jerome: You could say that. Now, if you don't mind, I must be going.
Jerome: Maybe you could help me pick out a uniform first?
Kittyeyes: So, that's what he meant by 'official business', huh? Didn't think it'd be so important.
Nolva: Come on, Kittyeyes, don't be so quick to judge him.
Jerome: I can't wear this!! It's way too gaudy!
Organiser: But this is the most popular uniform we have! Come on, it'll look great on you!
Jerome: What about that one? That one looks much more normal!
Organiser: Eh? But, this one is...
Jerome: It doesn't matter, just give me that one.
Kittyeyes: Eesh... Never would have thought that's the kind of stuff he was into...
Jerome: I'm sorry for making you wait.
Diana: ......
Jerome: Apologies for my outfit...
Diana: It's fine, this is a vacation spot after all.
Jerome: Where are your bodyguards, if you don't mind me asking?
Diana: Ah, they're all off somewhere else.
Jerome: Is that safe?
Diana: I'm used to it. To be honest, danger is danger, whether or not I've got my bodyguards around.
Jerome: I understand. Well, anyway, this is the letter Queen Angelia sent me here to give you.
Diana: Thank you, and sorry to have you come all this way. Here, let me buy you a drink.
Jerome: Ah, this really isn't necessary...
Diana: Oh please, I told you already, this is a vacation spot. Honestly I'd be more concerned if you didn't at least have a drink.
Jerome: Well, then, I graciously accept.
Diana: ...Now, I hear the Kingdom of the Sun has its affairs back in order?
Jerome: Yes, it does, all thanks to her majesty and our army.
Diana: Your army, hmm? Well, if only the Desert Kingdom's army could show such solidarity, our woes might be similarly alleviated.
Jerome: From what I've heard your kingdom's rebuilding efforts are going quite well.
Diana: Yes, it seems to be... and yet, here I am on vacation...
Jerome: Miss Diana, if you don't mind me saying...
Nolva: Hey, It's Jerome!
Jerome: Oh, it's you two! You've changed into your uniforms, I see.
Kittyeyes: Hehe~ Surprised?
Nolva: Oh, it's that pretty lady from before.
Diana: You two came with Jerome, right?
Diana: You must be his friends. Pleased to meet you, I'm Diana.
Kittyeyes: Friends? No, we're just...
Jerome: Yes, these are my friends. Meet Kittyeyes and Nolva.
Diana: Well then, why don't we all share a drink?
Nolva: Um... Is that alright?
Diana: Of course it's alright!
Kittyeyes: Friends!? What gives!?
Jerome: Sorry, I didn't know what to say... It's just easier if I say you're my friends for now.
Kittyeyes: Well, I'll play along for now, but this is a one-time deal!
Jerome: Thanks, Kittyeyes.
Kittyeyes: Well then, how about that drink, Diana~
Nolva: Kittyeyes?
Kittyeyes: It's okay, Nolva. We're here to have fun, aren't we?
Diana: Well, it seems they have all sorts of magnificent uniforms here!
Kittyeyes: They do! We couldn't make up our minds!
Diana: I especially like yours there, Nolva, it's quite unique.
Nolva: It is, isn't it? It gave me a sort of strange feeling when I looked at it... Does it look weird on me?
Diana: Not at all, it's cute! Very fitting!
Jerome: (Oh good, it seems like Diana's cheering up a bit.)
Team Captain: Get outta here! We're not teaming up with money-grubbing drunks like you!
Drunkard: Watch your mouth, ya *hic* trash heap... say that to my *hic* face!
Jerome: Watch out!
Nolva: What's wrong!?
Kittyeyes: These guys are drunk, be careful.
Diana: Everyone grab what's near you and defend yourselves!
Monkey Boy: Would ya quiet down or what!? I'm tryin' to enjoy a drink in peace over hea'!!
Drunkard: B-B-Boss...
Jerome: You're his boss?
Monkey Boy: So what if I am? Damn tourists think you can waltz in here and rough up my guys? You've got another thing comin'!
Kittyeyes: We never wanted to rough up anyone! They got drunk and started it!
Monkey Boy: Fuhgeddaboudit!! I saw it clear as day, don't try and bamboozle me! You provoked 'em first!
Monkey Boy: Excuse me!? You know what they call me? 'The Judge'! That's cause I'm never wrong! Damn, if I'm wrong I'll eat a banana with my nose!!
Team Captain: Hey, this's got nothin' to do with them! I've got beef with you and you only!!
Drunkard: Eh, don't worry, boss, I've got a banana right here *hic* for yous...
Monkey Boy: Aw, shut up all of ya! You're cruisin' for a bruisin', you are!
Team Captain: No reason to get indignant about it!
Monkey Boy: Only 'dignant piece a' boomshroom' eatin' butthead I see here is you!
Team Captain: You little...!!!
Kittyeyes: Hey, ape face! Don't forget about us all of a sudden!
Monkey Boy: Hmph!!
Monkey Boy: This should be enough money. Go buy some drinks.
Kittyeyes: Dumb monkey brain...
Monkey Boy: Aw shut up, will ya? I'm busy, alright? I've got no time for you!
Monkey Boy: Listen, since I'm a nice guy I'll forget about your little transgression here. Now, what do you think about that job?
Team Captain: Forget about it!!
Monkey Boy: Don't know when to give up, huh? What, you gonna try to run away?
Team Captain: You're one to talk! If you hadn't bought out our guys,
Team Captain: You dirty outsiders would never have a chance of beating us, the 'Glory of the Oasis'!!
Monkey Boy: I think somebody's being a sore loser!
Team Captain: I wouldn't be saying anything if I'd lost fair and square!
Team Captain: But you came in here screwing up all our trade, and getting rid of anyone who didn't join up with you!
Team Captain: You've made it so all the athletes here can barely get by!
Monkey Boy: There you go blaming me again. Remind me how you're not being a sore loser?
Team Captain: You...!! Gaghh, this time we'll beat you for sure!
Monkey Boy: Lotta bark, no bite! But it's alright, more fun to watch you lose that way!! Gyeahaha!!
Team Captain: We'll... definitely... beat you...!
Nolva: Are you alright?
Diana: ......
Team Captain: Damn! It's all about money! If we had enough, then our guys wouldn't be getting bought out!
Team Captain: Then everything'd be fine and I wouldn't be here getting so pissed off...
Diana: Get a hold of yourself!
Diana: Do go around blaming everything on money! It's pathetic! And you call yourself an athlete...
Team Captain: Huh!? W-What does a tourist like you know, anyway!
Team Captain: If I don't have any money, then I can't even train the athletes I do have! If we can't train, then we'll never stand a chance!
Diana: Oh yeah? So if you had money, then everything would change?
Team Captain: Of course... And if we won, then it would totally raise the morale here.
Team Captain: It'll tell the guys that... that we can do anything! With strength, you can overcome any hardship!
Diana: Well, if that's the case...
Diana: Would this be enough for you?
Kittyeyes: Diana...!?
Team Captain: Hmph! You rich folk are all the same!
Team Captain: I bet you're in cahoots with all the others, you're just trying to buy me out!
Kittyeyes: Hey, man, know a good opportunity when you see it.
Diana: It's alright, Kittyeyes. He's being defensive, and that shows me he's still got some fight left.
Diana: Listen, I'm not trying to 'buy you out', I'm just giving you a real chance to win.
Team Captain: What?
Diana: I'd like to be your sponsor. I want to help you get to the finish line.
Team Captain: But... what's in it for you?
Diana: Nothing, I just want to help.
Team Captain: Hmph, It's rare to meet someone as foolish as you.
Team Captain: But alright, I accept!
Jerome: If that's the case, then let me lend you a hand, too!
Diana: Jerome!?
Jerome: To be honest, I didn't like those thugs just now, either. Didn't sit right with me.
Kittyeyes: Me too! I wanna join up!

Kittyeyes: I couldn't stand those jerks, either!
What about you, Nolva?
Nolva: Eh? Uh... Yeah, I didn't like them either.
Diana: Thank you, everyone.
Kittyeyes: No need to thank us, we're friends~
Diana: Well then, let's get started!
